Only use '\circ' only for the functors 'precomposition' and 'postcomposition'
Use small latin letters for objects
Use capital latin letters for categories
Use capital latin letters for presheaves
Use \iso when we have an isomorphism and '=' when there is an equality
Use '=' when defining an object, instead of ':='.
Leave the topology implicit and refer to the category as if it is the site.
Define functors as a macro with optional argument.
Always use curly brackets to enclose argument of functor.
Make frequency table of macros.
Start every section with a plaintext introduction.
Natural transformations denoted by double arrows.(morphisms of presheaves not)
Lines no longer than 80 characters
Every 'statement'/sentence on a new line